Short Title: The Sober Operator Act of 2025. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Clampitt.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO ALLOW ONLY SOBER DRIVERS TO OPERATE VEHICLES AND VESSELS
3 AND SAVE LIVES OF OPERATORS, PASSENGERS, AND PEDESTRIANS BY
4 LOWERING THE ALCOHOL CONCENTRATION LEGAL LIMIT FOR OPERATING A
5 VEHICLE OR VESSEL FROM 0.08 TO 0.05; TO INCREASE EFFICIENCY IN THE
6 IMMEDIATE CIVIL PRETRIAL REVOCATION OF DRIVERS LICENSES; TO
7 REQUIRE IMPAIRED DRIVERS TO PAY THEIR FAIR SHARE OF THE COSTS OF
8 THEIR PROCESSING; TO REDUCE UNNECESSARY MOTIONS BY ADMITTING
9 ALCOHOL AND DRUG SCREENING TESTS TO PROVE THE ARRESTING OFFICER
10 HAD PROBABLE CAUSE; TO ASSURE TRANSPARENCY IN THE COURTS SO THAT
11 ALL OPERATORS ARE TREATED EQUALLY AND ALL USERS OF THE STREETS
12 AND WATERWAYS THROUGHOUT THE STATE HAVE EQUAL PROTECTION
13 FROM IMPAIRED DRIVERS BY REQUIRING VIDEO RECORDING OF DISTRICT
14 COURT PROCEEDINGS AND PUBLISHING REPORTS OF HOW IMPAIRED
15 DRIVING CASES ARE RESOLVED; TO ALLOW REPEAT OFFENDERS A METHOD
16 TO PROVE THEIR SOBRIETY AND OBTAIN A LEGAL METHOD TO OPERATE A
17 VEHICLE; AND TO REVISE THE PUNISHMENT IMPOSED ON A PERSON OVER
18 LAWFUL AGE WHO AIDS AND ABETS A PERSON UNDER LAWFUL AGE IN THE
19 SALE OR PURCHASE OF ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES IF SERIOUS BODILY INJURY
20 RESULTS.
21 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
22
23 TITLE OF ACT
24 SECTION 1. This act shall be known as "The Sober Operator Act of 2025."
25
26 REVISIONS RELATING TO LOWERING THE ALCOHOL CONCENTRATION
27 LEGAL LIMIT FROM 0.08 TO 0.05 WHEN OPERATING A VEHICLE OR VESSEL
28 AND INCREASE EFFICIENCY IN ADMINISTERING THE IMMEDIATE CIVIL
29 PRETRIAL REVOCATION
