23 (a1) Meaning of Terms. – Under this section, an "implied-consent offense" is an offense
24 involving impaired driving, a violation of G.S. 20-141.4(a2), or an alcohol-related offense made
25 subject to the procedures of this section. A person is "charged" with an offense if the person is
26 arrested for it or if criminal process for the offense has been issued. The term "judicial official"
27 is as defined in G.S. 15A-101.
28 …
