36 "(b5) Subsequent Tests Allowed. – A person may be requested, pursuant to G.S. 20-16.2,
37 to submit to a chemical analysis of the person's blood or other bodily fluid or substance in
38 addition to or in lieu of a chemical analysis of the breath, in the discretion of a law enforcement
39 officer; except that a person charged with a violation of G.S. 20-141.4 shall be requested, at any
40 relevant time after the driving, to provide a blood sample in addition to or in lieu of a chemical
41 analysis of the breath. However, if a breath sample shows an alcohol concentration of .08 0.05
42 or more, then requesting a blood sample shall be in the discretion of a law enforcement officer.
43 If a subsequent chemical analysis is requested pursuant to this subsection, the person shall again
44 be advised of the implied consent rights in accordance with G.S. 20-16.2(a). A person's willful
45 refusal to submit to a chemical analysis of the blood or other bodily fluid or substance is a willful
46 refusal under G.S. 20-16.2. If a person willfully refuses to provide a blood sample under this
47 subsection, and the person is charged with a violation of G.S. 20-141.4, then a law enforcement
48 officer with probable cause to believe that the offense involved impaired driving or was an
49 alcohol-related offense made subject to the procedures of G.S. 20-16.2 shall seek a warrant to
50 obtain a blood sample. The failure to obtain a blood sample pursuant to this subsection shall not
51 be grounds for the dismissal of a charge and is not an appealable issue."
